## Overview

The Job Cycle page sits under Analytics → Job Cycle. It tracks how many items were scraped/processed per day across 28-day cycles. Each cycle has rows for each weekday job (VVIP, Links Input, New Items, etc.). The user edits the # (count) column after completing work, marks the row as Done, and the system auto-calculates payment at $0.01 per item.

---

## Cycle Rules

### Cycle 17 (Historical)
- Hardcoded from Google Sheet data
- Start: 16/02/2026, End: 13/03/2026
- 23 seed rows with pre-filled counts
- Job types include legacy types: VIP, 5001-6250, 6251-7500

### Cycle 18 Onwards (Auto-Generated)
- Start date: Cycle 18 = 16/03/2026
- Each subsequent cycle starts exactly **28 days** after the previous
- End date displayed on cycle card = last Friday within the 28-day window
- Rows auto-generated based on fixed weekday schedule (see [Job Type Schedule](#job-type-schedule))
- Weekends (Sat/Sun) are skipped — no rows generated

### Cycle Start Date Formula
```
Cycle 17: Feb 16, 2026 (hardcoded)
Cycle 18: Mar 16, 2026
Cycle N (N >= 18): Mar 16, 2026 + (N - 18) × 28 days
```

