## API Endpoints

### GET /api/job-cycle
**No params**: Returns all distinct cycle numbers `[17, 18, 19, ...]`
**With `?cycle=17`**: Returns all rows for that cycle, ordered by date + job type

### POST /api/job-cycle
Add a single row manually.
```json
{ "cycle": 18, "job_date": "2026-03-20", "job_type": "VVIP" }
```
Returns updated cycle rows. Logs `create_row` to history.

### POST /api/job-cycle/generate
Generate all rows for a new cycle (Cycle 18+).
```json
{ "cycle": 19 }
```
Uses `INSERT IGNORE` to prevent duplicates. Returns generated rows.

### PATCH /api/job-cycle/:id
Update one field per request. Only one of `count`, `done`, or `hidden` allowed.
```json
{ "count": 1500 }
// or
{ "done": true }
// or
{ "hidden": true }
```
Returns `{ success: true }` or `{ success: true, noChange: true }` if value didn't change.

### GET /api/job-cycle/:id
Returns last 20 history log entries for this row from `history_logs` table.

